{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"04cd4140-8272-4d53-9a41-8427508ac8f4","content":"The migration is straightforward. In your project file, **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` 3.8 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so simply removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` switches you over.\n\n**Key things to know after switching:**\n\n1. **Running tests** — `dotnet test` still works, but you can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) since it now produces an executable.\n2. **CLI differences** — filter syntax changes from `--filter` to `--filter` with a slightly different expression format. Check `dotnet test -- --help` for options.\n3. **Code coverage / loggers** — if you use VSTest adapters (e.g., Coverlet VSTest collector, TRX logger), you'll need the Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents:\n   - TRX reports → add `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` is already implicit; TRX is built-in via `--report-trx`.\n   - Coverlet → use `coverlet.collector` with the new platform or Microsoft's `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` package.\n4. **CI pipelines** — replace any `--logger trx` arguments with `-- --report-trx` (arguments after `--` are forwarded to the new platform).\n5. **`.runsettings`** — still supported via `dotnet test -s my.runsettings`.\n\n**TL;DR:** Just delete the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` line — the SDK handles the rest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6edfbd07-f26b-4b09-aafc-94f210dc0860","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. This is a general knowledge question, not related to files in the working directory. Let me answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and Microsoft.Testing.Platform migration.","outputTokens":528,"requestId":"7C10:203FDB:266DD6E:2A7E75F:69F93FDB"},"id":"04e6c51a-376b-4362-973d-87385c9244d4","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:55:03.979Z","parentId":"c2817fa4-890d-4e18-81c4-6f93f65d10f3"}
